items.name: AngelStatueTECH
items.description:
Ever wanted your everything to be more angelic ? Here's the answer.

This one is pretty responsive to prompts but also VERY random in what you'll get :D That's crazy filigree for you. It's loosely based on the konyconi style so it can do a bit of everything.

Resolution

This works best at higher resolution and with a large number of steps because of the detail. You don't have to go nuts, 30-40 on SDE 2++ Karras is fine but the default 12-20 on that sampler will be pretty gross.

Prompting

Main keyword: 4ng3lt3ch

Other terms I recommend playing with are wings,filigree,intricate,angelic if the style isn't applying very well to a prompt.

Note: I did train batman statues into the data... but it seems to fight the model (at least with REVanimated) so I dont recommend using it unless you want to battle prompts

If you like it, please review it or;

items.name: Zooey (Granblue Fantasy)
items.description:
I'm testing out the Dadaptation optimizer as outlined in this guide: https://rentry.co/dadaptguide

The results seem pretty good, though I'm definitely running into some problems from my inexperience. I think I included too many NSFW images in the training set, since any prompting outside of her two main outfits will more often than not leave her topless. Eye color also needs to be specified since that wasn't consistent throughout the training data either. Still working on how many steps looks accurate without overfitting. I'm including two versions so people can use them as they like.

Trained for two main outfits:

Regular:

zooey_reg, armor, gloves, thighhighs, breastplate, blue skirt, bare shoulders

Summer:

zooey_summer, swimsuit, hair flower, bikini, frilled bikini

General helpful tags:

tan, dark skin, dark-skinned female, red eyes, long hair, hair between eyes

So far it favors her summer look, so add "head flower" to negatives to remove it.

items.name: Female Horror - AutoPrompt - Awesome prompt lists
items.description:
A suggestion a while ago was made for vampires and horror prompts. I've tried to recreate some of these while trying to get somewhat consistent "horror" elements from SD. If you guys see parts of the prompts that are bad please comment so that I can improve it

Description

Useful for when you want to create images and later go through and pick out the best creations. These prompts are randomly generated every time I generate new lists.

I use them in conjunction with a stable diffusion image viewer I have written where I view thousands of images I've created to find:

  1. Good prompts that have an art style I like

  2. Good prompts that create really good images

  3. Good compositions 👏

Dataset description

  • Combination list contains prompts from both lists

  • Example prompt for female_horror_fantasy: unsettling, Brilliant yet deranged scientist, Fair Skin, Redhead with half-up half-down style and loose curls, brown sheer lipstick, A moonlit lake with a silhouette lurking just beneath the surface

  • Example prompt for female_horror_landscape: unsettling, Brilliant yet deranged scientist, Fair Skin, Redhead with half-up half-down style and loose curls, brown sheer lipstick, A moonlit lake with a silhouette lurking just beneath the surface

  • Example prompt for female_horror_magical_creature: unsettling, Brilliant yet deranged scientist, Fair Skin, Redhead with half-up half-down style and loose curls, brown sheer lipstick, A moonlit lake with a silhouette lurking just beneath the surface, centaur

  • Example prompt for female_horror_creature: unsettling, Brilliant yet deranged scientist, Fair Skin, Redhead with half-up half-down style and loose curls, brown sheer lipstick, A moonlit lake with a silhouette lurking just beneath the surface

  • Example prompt for female_horror_creatures_portrait: portrait, unsettling, Brilliant yet deranged scientist, Fair Skin, Redhead with half-up half-down style and loose curls, brown sheer lipstick, with a desert oasis in the background

Feedback

If you got feedback just comment.

Usage

  1. Open automatic1111 SD / any other SD creation tool with similar prompt file input

  2. Select <Script> --> Prompts from file or textbox

  3. Drop file or copy paste contents in the "List of prompts inputs"

  4. To view information on images you have created you can use "PNG Info" tab in Automatic1111.

items.name: Accent Wall - Stucco Radici dell’albero
items.description:
Combining Italian-born stucco paint and advanced Japanese construction techniques, Stucco Plus Inc( https://stuccoplus.co.jp ). is developing the fascination of singular plaster finishes in the digital world. Our unique finishing technique is presented as the Lora model, allowing you to give shape to your imagination. This project, which is still growing, will continue to evolve alongside our technology.

Using SegmentAnything and Inpaint together, you can draw a lively perspective image of your home before and after the renovation. Seeing the remodelling image change in real time will help you realise your ideal space. When your creativity is inspired, please share your work with us. We look forward to seeing your ideas.

The model being presented to the public is called 'Radici dell'albero' (Root of the tree) and is an exclusive finish using Grassello Metaluce. Inspired by the natural world, this technique expresses the undulation and depth of tree roots in a space. It brings a unique texture and depth to your space in your quest for luxury and dynamism.

A strength of 0.7-0.8 is recommended.

イタリア生まれの漆喰塗料と、日本の高度な施工技術を組み合わせた株式会社スタッコプラス( https://stuccoplus.co.jp )は、特異な左官仕上げの魅力をデジタル世界に展開しています。私たちの独特の仕上げ技術をLoraモデルとして公開し、あなたの想像を形にすることを可能にします。まだ成長途中のこのプロジェクトは、私たちの技術と共に進化し続けます。

SegmentAnythingとInpaintを共に使用することで、リフォームの前後を生き生きとしたパース画像で描くことができます。リアルタイムで変化するリフォームイメージを見て、あなたの理想の空間を具現化する一助となることでしょう。創造力を刺激された作品が出来上がったら、是非弊社にシェアして下さい。私たちはあなたのアイデアを見るのを楽しみにしています。

この公開されるモデルは、「Radici dell’albero」（木の根）と名付けられ、Grassello Metaluceを用いた独自の仕上げです。自然界からインスピレーションを得たこの技法は、木の根のようなうねりと深みを空間に表現します。豪華さとダイナミズムを追求するあなたの空間に、独特のテクスチャと深遠さをもたらします。

Lora強度は0.7-0.8がおすすめです。

items.name: MH-6 Little Bird (1963)
items.description:
Delta rode in on benches outside the bubble frames of the four MH-6 Little Birds, each chopper carrying a four-man team. They wore big black flak vests and plastic hockey helmets over a radio earplug and a wraparound microphone that kept them in constant voice contact with each other. They wore no insignias on their uniforms.
Hanging out over the street on their low, fast approach, they scanned the people below, their upturned startled faces, their hands, their demeanor, trying to read what would happen when they hit the street. As the Little Birds came in, the crowd spooked. People and cars began to scatter. Wind from the powerful rotors knocked some people down and tore the colorful robes off some of the women. A few of the Rangers, still high overhead, spotted people below gesturing up at them eagerly, as if inviting them to come down to the streets and fight.
